-- Colombia’s Bolsa de Valores First-Quarter Profit Increases 40%
-- B y   C h r i s t i n e   J e n k i n s
-- 2012-04-17T17:19:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-17/colombia-s-bolsa-de-valores-first-quarter-profit-increases-40-.html
Bolsa de Valores de Colombia SA ,
the operator of the country’s main stock exchange, said net
income increased 40 percent to 11.5 billion pesos ($6.5 million)
in the first three months of the year.  Operating revenue climbed 18 percent to 19 billion pesos,
the company said in a statement posted on its website yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Christine Jenkins in New York at 
